                        <h1>Where Did My Tooth Enamel Go?</h1>

                        <h2><em>Yes, that LaCroix may actually be killing your teeth.</em></h2>
                        
                        <p>
                            There are many reasons to want to whiten your teeth &ndash; but before you look at the how, let&rsquo;s 
                            look at why you got to this place.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            Tooth enamel is a finite substance that can be worn down by foods, drinks, and smoking. It may be the 
                            hardest stuff in the human body, but it still maxes out at 2mm thick. Enamel is also a mineral, so it 
                            can&rsquo;t grow back. That means all of the erosion from food, drinks (yes, even LaCroix), and other 
                            factors is permanent.
                        </p>

                    </div>
